#: ../../tips_and_tricks/tips_and_tricks/default_transition_duration.rst:17
msgid ""
"You can configure the default duration for all newly created transitions. In "
"versions prior to 16.08, all new transitions were always 65 frames long - "
"and this translated to varying default durations, depending on a project's "
"frame rate. This new configuration option should appeal to all those users "
"who work a lot with transitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/tips_and_tricks/default_transition_duration.rst:25
msgid ":menuselection:`Menu --> Settings --> Configure Kdenlive`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/tips_and_tricks/default_transition_duration.rst:27
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Menu --> Settings --> Configure Kdenlive --> Misc`. "
"Under the heading :guilabel:`Default Durations` you will find the option to "
"configure the default duration for newly created transitions. Enter a "
"duration in the usual format :abbr:`hh:mm:ss:ff (hours:minutes:seconds:"
"frames)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/tips_and_tricks/default_transition_duration.rst:29
msgid ""
"Please note that the frames (**ff**) field element will be interpreted on "
"the basis of the current project's framerate. In contrast, the other field "
"elements (**hh:mm:ss**) are independent of the framerate."
msgstr ""

